    "SUMMARY": "Martin Jedlička (born 24 January 1998) is a Czech professional footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for Viktoria Plzeň.\nHe made his league debut in Mladá Boleslav's Czech First League 0–3 loss at Sparta Prague on 3 December 2017. On his debut, he scored an own goal in the 12th minute by misjudging Eidar Civić's cross, parrying the ball into the goalpost and then deflecting it into his own net. This was the first Czech First League goal to be confirmed by video review."
